  1 | # debug-joint
  2 | 
  3 | **Purpose:** Diagnose why a specific joint isn't responding to commands.
  4 | 
  5 | **Usage:** `/debug-joint <joint_name>`
  6 | 
  7 | **Example:** `/debug-joint l_hip_pitch`
  8 | 
  9 | ---
 10 | 
 11 | ## What This Command Does
 12 | 
 13 | Given a joint name (e.g., `l_hip_pitch`, `r_knee`, `l_ankle`), this command traces the complete signal path from Python controller to physical joint movement, checking every configuration point where the joint could fail.
 14 | 
 15 | ---
 16 | 
 17 | ## Diagnostic Checklist
 18 | 
 19 | ### 1. **SDF Joint Definition** (`worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf`)
 20 | 
 21 | **Check:**
 22 | - Joint exists in `<model name="ArduBiped_Proto">`
 23 | - Joint type: `revolute` (movable) or `fixed` (immovable)
 24 | - Joint limits: `<lower>` and `<upper>` bounds
 25 | - Joint axis: `<xyz>` direction vector
 26 | - Joint dynamics: `<damping>` and `<friction>` values
 27 | - Initial position: `<initial_position>` value
 28 | 
 29 | **Common Issues:**
 30 | - **Fixed joint:** If `type="fixed"`, joint cannot move (e.g., ankle joints)
 31 | - **Inverted limits:** `<lower>` > `<upper>` causes Gazebo errors
 32 | - **Zero damping:** Can cause oscillations or instability
 33 | - **Duplicate friction tags:** Lines 193, 201, 209, 220, 228, 236 have duplicates (Gazebo uses last value)
 34 | 
 35 | **Search Pattern:**
 36 | ```xml
 37 | <joint name="<joint_name>" type="revolute">
 38 |   <pose>...</pose>
 39 |   <parent>...</parent>
 40 |   <child>...</child>
 41 |   <axis>
 42 |     <xyz>...</xyz>
 43 |     <limit>
 44 |       <lower>-1.571</lower>
 45 |       <upper>0.523</upper>
 46 |     </limit>
 47 |     <dynamics>
 48 |       <damping>0.1</damping>
 49 |       <friction>0.5</friction>
 50 |     </dynamics>
 51 |   </axis>
 52 | </joint>
 53 | ```
 54 | 
 55 | ---
 56 | 
 57 | ### 2. **Gazebo Joint Controller** (`worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf`)
 58 | 
 59 | **Check:**
 60 | - Plugin exists: `<plugin filename="gz-sim-joint-position-controller-system">`
 61 | - Joint name matches: `<joint_name>` tag
 62 | - Topic name: `<topic>` (should be `/<joint_name>/cmd`)
 63 | - PID gains: `<p_gain>8</p_gain>`, `<i_gain>0.01</i_gain>`, `<d_gain>10</d_gain>`
 64 | - Initial target: `<initial_position>` (should match standing pose)
 65 | 
 66 | **Common Issues:**
 67 | - **Topic mismatch:** Topic name doesn't match what Python publishes to
 68 | - **Low P gain:** P < 5 causes sluggish response (model.sdf has P=5, world file has P=8)
 69 | - **Missing plugin:** Controller not loaded, joint won't respond
 70 | - **Wrong initial position:** Robot falls immediately on spawn
 71 | 
 72 | **Search Pattern:**
 73 | ```xml
 74 | <plugin filename="gz-sim-joint-position-controller-system" name="gz::sim::systems::JointPositionController">
 75 |   <joint_name>l_hip_pitch</joint_name>
 76 |   <topic>/l_hip_pitch/cmd</topic>
 77 |   <p_gain>8</p_gain>
 78 |   <i_gain>0.01</i_gain>
 79 |   <d_gain>10</d_gain>
 80 |   <initial_position>-0.09</initial_position>
 81 | </plugin>
 82 | ```
 83 | 
 84 | ---
 85 | 
 86 | ### 3. **ArduPilotPlugin Channel Mapping** (`worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf`)
 87 | 
 88 | **Check:**
 89 | - Plugin exists: `<plugin filename="ArduPilotPlugin" name="ardupilot_plugin">`
 90 | - Channel mapping: `<control channel="N">` block
 91 | - Joint name matches: `<jointName>` tag
 92 | - Multiplier: `<multiplier>` (converts PWM range to angle range)
 93 | - Offset: `<offset>` (shifts neutral point)
 94 | - PWM limits: `<servo_min>1000</servo_min>`, `<servo_max>2000</servo_max>`
 95 | 
 96 | **PWM Conversion Formula:**
 97 | ```
 98 | angle = (pwm - 1500) / 500 * multiplier + offset
 99 | ```
100 | 
101 | **Channel Mapping (Current):**
102 | - CH0 → `l_hip_pitch` (mult=1.571, offset=-0.5)
103 | - CH1 → `r_hip_pitch` (mult=1.571, offset=-0.5)
104 | - CH2 → `l_knee` (mult=2.618, offset=-0.5)
105 | - CH3 → `r_knee` (mult=2.618, offset=-0.5)
106 | - CH4-CH7 → **NOT MAPPED** (hip_roll joints don't exist yet)
107 | 
108 | **Common Issues:**
109 | - **Joint not mapped:** Only 4 channels configured (hip_pitch, knee only)
110 | - **Wrong multiplier:** Doesn't match joint limits (hip: 1.571 rad = 90°, knee: 2.618 rad = 150°)
111 | - **Offset confusion:** Offset shifts neutral point, not just range (PWM 1500 → angle = offset)
112 | - **Ankle joints:** Fixed joints, commands ignored even if mapped
113 | 
114 | **Search Pattern:**
115 | ```xml
116 | <control channel="0">
117 |   <jointName>l_hip_pitch</jointName>
118 |   <multiplier>1.571</multiplier>
119 |   <offset>-0.5</offset>
120 |   <servo_min>1000</servo_min>
121 |   <servo_max>2000</servo_max>
122 | </control>
123 | ```
124 | 
125 | ---
126 | 
127 | ### 4. **Python Controller Commands** (`scripts/gait_controller.py`, `scripts/balance_controller.py`)
128 | 
129 | **Check:**
130 | - Topic publisher exists: `gz.transport.Node().advertise()`
131 | - Topic name matches: `/<joint_name>/cmd`
132 | - Message type: `gz.msgs.Double`
133 | - Command within limits: Check against SDF joint limits
134 | - Controller running: Process active and connected to MAVLink
135 | 
136 | **Common Issues:**
137 | - **Topic name typo:** Python publishes to wrong topic
138 | - **No subscriber:** Gazebo plugin not loaded (run `check_config.py`)
139 | - **Command out of bounds:** Joint limits violated, Gazebo clamps or explodes
140 | - **Controller not running:** `startup.sh` or `gait_controller.py` not started
141 | - **Multiple controllers:** Two scripts fighting for control (e.g., `balance_controller.py` + `gait_controller.py`)
142 | 
143 | **Standing Pose (Canonical):**
144 | ```python
145 | HIP_STAND  = -0.09  # rad
146 | KNEE_STAND =  0.35  # rad
147 | ANKLE_STAND = 0.0   # rad (fixed joint, ignored)
148 | ```
149 | 
150 | **Search Pattern in Python:**
151 | ```python
152 | topic = f"/{joint_name}/cmd"
153 | pub = node.advertise(topic, gz.msgs.Double)
154 | msg = gz.msgs.Double()
155 | msg.data = angle  # Must be within joint limits
156 | pub.publish(msg)
157 | ```
158 | 
159 | ---
160 | 
161 | ### 5. **Joint Limits Consistency** (`inverse_kinematics.py` vs SDF)
162 | 
163 | **Check:**
164 | - IK solver limits match SDF limits
165 | - Ankle compensation formula: `ankle = -(hip_pitch + knee*0.3)`
166 | - Leg lengths: L1=L2=0.20m (thigh/shin)
167 | 
168 | **IK Solver Limits:**
169 | ```python
170 | hip_pitch: [-1.57, 0.52] rad  (-90° to +30°)
171 | knee:      [0.0, 2.618] rad   (0° to +150°)
172 | ankle:     [-0.5, 0.5] rad
173 | hip_roll:  [-0.4, 0.4] rad    (NOT IN CURRENT MODEL)
174 | ```
175 | 
176 | **Common Issues:**
177 | - **Limit mismatch:** IK solver allows angles SDF rejects
178 | - **Knee hyperextension:** IK solver clamped at line 17, but check commands
179 | - **Hip roll commands:** ZMP controller sends hip_roll, but joints don't exist
180 | 
181 | ---
182 | 
183 | ### 6. **Gazebo Topic Verification** (`scripts/check_config.py`)
184 | 
185 | **Run:**
186 | ```bash
187 | cd scripts
188 | python3 check_config.py
189 | ```
190 | 
191 | **Expected Output:**
192 | ```
193 | Checking /l_hip_pitch/cmd... ✓ (1 subscriber)
194 | Checking /r_hip_pitch/cmd... ✓ (1 subscriber)
195 | Checking /l_knee/cmd... ✓ (1 subscriber)
196 | Checking /r_knee/cmd... ✓ (1 subscriber)
197 | Checking /l_ankle/cmd... ✓ (1 subscriber)
198 | Checking /r_ankle/cmd... ✓ (1 subscriber)
199 | ```
200 | 
201 | **Common Issues:**
202 | - **0 subscribers:** ArduPilotPlugin not loaded, restart Gazebo
203 | - **Script fails:** Gazebo not running or wrong version
204 | 
205 | ---
206 | 
207 | ### 7. **ArduPilot Parameter Check** (`mav.parm`)
208 | 
209 | **Check (if using ArduPilot servo output):**
210 | - Servo function: `SERVON_FUNCTION` (N = channel number)
211 | - Servo min/max: `SERVON_MIN`, `SERVON_MAX`
212 | - Servo trim: `SERVON_TRIM=1500`
213 | 
214 | **Current Status:**
215 | - **Python bypasses ArduPilot:** Controllers publish directly to Gazebo topics
216 | - **ArduPilot servo output unused:** Intended architecture not implemented yet
217 | - **Lua scripting not integrated:** No Lua scripts generating servo commands
218 | 
219 | **Note:** This check only matters for future Lua-based control.
220 | 
221 | ---
222 | 
223 | ## Diagnostic Workflow
224 | 
225 | ### Step 1: Identify Joint Type
226 | ```bash
227 | # Search SDF for joint definition
228 | grep -A 20 'joint name="<joint_name>"' worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf
229 | ```
230 | 
231 | **If `type="fixed"`:** Joint cannot move. Ankle joints are fixed by design.
232 | 
233 | ---
234 | 
235 | ### Step 2: Verify Gazebo Controller
236 | ```bash
237 | # Search for joint controller plugin
238 | grep -A 10 '<joint_name><joint_name></joint_name>' worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf
239 | ```
240 | 
241 | **Check:**
242 | - Plugin exists
243 | - Topic name matches `/<joint_name>/cmd`
244 | - PID gains reasonable (P=8, I=0.01, D=10)
245 | 
246 | ---
247 | 
248 | ### Step 3: Check Topic Subscribers
249 | ```bash
250 | cd scripts
251 | python3 check_config.py
252 | ```
253 | 
254 | **If 0 subscribers:** Restart Gazebo, plugin not loaded.
255 | 
256 | ---
257 | 
258 | ### Step 4: Verify Python Commands
259 | ```bash
260 | # Search Python scripts for joint commands
261 | grep -r "<joint_name>" scripts/*.py
262 | ```
263 | 
264 | **Check:**
265 | - Topic name matches Gazebo controller
266 | - Commands within joint limits
267 | - Controller process running
268 | 
269 | ---
270 | 
271 | ### Step 5: Test Manual Command
272 | ```bash
273 | # Publish test command to Gazebo topic
274 | gz topic -t /<joint_name>/cmd -m gz.msgs.Double -p "data: 0.0"
275 | ```
276 | 
277 | **If joint moves:** Python controller issue (topic name, limits, or not running).
278 | **If joint doesn't move:** Gazebo controller issue (plugin not loaded, wrong topic, or fixed joint).
279 | 
280 | ---
281 | 
282 | ### Step 6: Check ArduPilotPlugin Mapping
283 | ```bash
284 | # Search for channel mapping
285 | grep -A 10 '<jointName><joint_name></jointName>' worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf
286 | ```
287 | 
288 | **Note:** Only matters if using ArduPilot servo output (not current architecture).
289 | 
290 | ---
291 | 
292 | ## Common Joint-Specific Issues
293 | 
294 | ### `l_ankle` / `r_ankle`
295 | - **Type:** `fixed` joint (cannot move)
296 | - **Commands ignored:** Python sends commands, but Gazebo ignores them
297 | - **IK solver:** Still computes ankle compensation, but has no effect
298 | - **Fix:** None needed, this is by design
299 | 
300 | ### `l_hip_pitch` / `r_hip_pitch`
301 | - **Most common issue:** Initial position mismatch (world file: -0.09, some scripts: -0.05, -0.10, -0.2)
302 | - **PWM mapping:** CH0/CH1, multiplier=1.571, offset=-0.5
303 | - **Limits:** [-1.571, 0.523] rad (-90° to +30°)
304 | 
305 | ### `l_knee` / `r_knee`
306 | - **Most common issue:** Hyperextension (knee < 0)
307 | - **PWM mapping:** CH2/CH3, multiplier=2.618, offset=-0.5
308 | - **Limits:** [0.0, 2.618] rad (0° to +150°)
309 | - **IK clamping:** Line 17 in `inverse_kinematics.py`
310 | 
311 | ### `l_hip_roll` / `r_hip_roll`
312 | - **Status:** **DOES NOT EXIST** in current model
313 | - **ZMP controller:** Requires these joints, will fail
314 | - **Fix required:** Add to SDF model (see AGENTS.md Next Steps #1)
315 | 
316 | ---
317 | 
318 | ## Quick Reference
319 | 
320 | ### Joint Limits (SDF)
321 | ```
322 | l_hip_pitch:  [-1.571, 0.523] rad  (-90° to +30°)
323 | l_knee:       [0.0, 2.618] rad     (0° to +150°)
324 | l_knee_shin:  [0.0, 2.618] rad     (0° to +150°)
325 | l_ankle:      fixed (no limits)
326 | ```
327 | 
328 | ### Standing Pose (Canonical)
329 | ```python
330 | HIP_STAND  = -0.09  # rad
331 | KNEE_STAND =  0.35  # rad
332 | ANKLE_STAND = 0.0   # rad
333 | ```
334 | 
335 | ### Gazebo Topics
336 | ```
337 | /l_hip_pitch/cmd
338 | /r_hip_pitch/cmd
339 | /l_knee/cmd
340 | /r_knee/cmd
341 | /l_ankle/cmd  (fixed joint, ignored)
342 | /r_ankle/cmd  (fixed joint, ignored)
343 | ```
344 | 
345 | ### ArduPilot Channel Mapping
346 | ```
347 | CH0 → l_hip_pitch
348 | CH1 → r_hip_pitch
349 | CH2 → l_knee
350 | CH3 → r_knee
351 | CH4-CH7 → NOT MAPPED
352 | ```
353 | 
354 | ---
355 | 
356 | ## Files to Check
357 | 
358 | 1. [`worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf`](worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf) - Joint definitions, controllers, ArduPilotPlugin
359 | 2. [`scripts/gait_controller.py`](scripts/gait_controller.py) - Gait commands, balance PID
360 | 3. [`scripts/balance_controller.py`](scripts/balance_controller.py) - Standing balance commands
361 | 4. [`scripts/inverse_kinematics.py`](scripts/inverse_kinematics.py) - IK solver, joint limits
362 | 5. [`scripts/check_config.py`](scripts/check_config.py) - Topic subscriber verification
363 | 6. [`mav.parm`](mav.parm) - ArduPilot parameters (if using servo output)
364 | 
365 | ---
366 | 
367 | **End of debug-joint command**
</content>
