593 | ## ZMP Stability Theory
594 | 
595 | ### Linear Inverted Pendulum Model (LIPM)
596 | 
597 | **Assumptions:**
598 | 1. CoM moves in horizontal plane at constant height
599 | 2. All mass concentrated at CoM
600 | 3. Legs are massless
601 | 4. No angular momentum about CoM
602 | 
603 | **Dynamics:**
604 | ```
605 | com_ddot = (g / h) * (com - zmp)
606 | 
607 | where:
608 |   com = Center of Mass position (x, y)
609 |   zmp = Zero Moment Point position (x, y)
610 |   g = 9.81 m/s² (gravity)
611 |   h = 0.38 m (CoM height)
612 |   omega = sqrt(g/h) = 5.07 rad/s (natural frequency)
613 | ```
614 | 
615 | **ZMP Equation:**
616 | ```
617 | zmp = com - (h / g) * com_ddot
618 | 
619 | For stable walking:
620 |   zmp must stay within support polygon
621 | ```
622 | 
623 | **Support Polygon:**
624 | - Single support: Foot contact area
625 | - Double support: Convex hull of both feet
626 | - Safety margin: 0.02m from edges
627 | 
628 | ### Preview Control
629 | 
630 | **Concept:** Use future ZMP reference to compute optimal CoM trajectory.
631 | 
632 | **Preview Horizon:** N = 20 steps (0.4s at 50 Hz)
633 | 
634 | **Cost Function:**
635 | ```
636 | J = Σ (Qe * e_k² + R * u_k²)
637 | 
638 | where:
639 |   e_k = zmp_ref[k] - zmp[k]  (tracking error)
640 |   u_k = com_accel[k]          (control input)
641 |   Qe = 1.0                    (tracking weight)
642 |   R = 1e-6                    (control weight)
643 | ```
644 | 
645 | **Optimal Control:**
646 | ```
647 | u = -K_x * state + Σ K_p[i] * zmp_ref[k+i]
648 | 
649 | where:
650 |   K_x = state feedback gains
651 |   K_p = preview gains (computed from DARE solution)
652 | ```
