  1 | # lua-trace
  2 | 
  3 | **Purpose:** Trace the complete signal flow from an ArduPilot servo channel to its physical joint, showing every file and transformation.
  4 | 
  5 | **Usage:** `/lua-trace <channel_number>`
  6 | 
  7 | **Example:** `/lua-trace 0`
  8 | 
  9 | ---
 10 | 
 11 | ## What This Command Does
 12 | 
 13 | Given an ArduPilot servo channel number (0-7), this command traces the complete signal path from Lua script generation through ArduPilot servo output, ArduPilotPlugin PWM conversion, Gazebo joint controller, and finally to physical joint movement. Shows every file touched, every transformation applied, and every configuration point.
 14 | 
 15 | ---
 16 | 
 17 | ## Signal Flow Overview
 18 | 
 19 | ```
 20 | ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 21 | │ 1. LUA SCRIPT (Future - Not Yet Implemented)                   │
 22 | │    File: scripts/humanoid.lua (DOES NOT EXIST YET)             │
 23 | │    - Reads MAVLink commands (GUIDED mode, waypoints)            │
 24 | │    - Implements ZMP preview control + IK                         │
 25 | │    - Generates joint angles                                      │
 26 | │    - Converts angles → PWM (reverse of plugin formula)           │
 27 | │    - Outputs to SRV_Channels                                     │
 28 | └────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 29 |                  │
 30 |                  │ SRV_Channel API
 31 |                  │ SRV_Channels:set_output_pwm(channel, pwm)
 32 |                  │
 33 | ┌────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 34 | │ 2. ARDUPILOT ROVER SITL                                         │
 35 | │    File: mav.parm (ArduPilot parameters)                        │
 36 | │    - Receives servo commands from Lua                            │
 37 | │    - Applies servo parameters (min/max/trim/function)            │
 38 | │    - Outputs PWM values (1000-2000 µs)                           │
 39 | │    - Sends via JSON protocol to ArduPilotPlugin                  │
 40 | │                                                                  │
 41 | │    Key Parameters:                                               │
 42 | │    - SERVO<N>_FUNCTION: Channel assignment                       │
 43 | │    - SERVO<N>_MIN: 1000 (minimum PWM)                            │
 44 | │    - SERVO<N>_MAX: 2000 (maximum PWM)                            │
 45 | │    - SERVO<N>_TRIM: 1500 (neutral PWM)                           │
 46 | └────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 47 |                  │
 48 |                  │ JSON Protocol (127.0.0.1:9002)
 49 |                  │ {"servo<N>": pwm_value}
 50 |                  │
 51 | ┌────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 52 | │ 3. ARDUPILOT PLUGIN (Gazebo Plugin)                            │
 53 | │    File: worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf                          │
 54 | │    Plugin: ArduPilotPlugin                                       │
 55 | │    - Receives PWM from ArduPilot via JSON                        │
 56 | │    - Looks up channel mapping in <control channel="N">           │
 57 | │    - Applies PWM → angle conversion formula                      │
 58 | │    - Publishes angle to Gazebo topic                             │
 59 | │                                                                  │
 60 | │    PWM → Angle Formula:                                          │
 61 | │    angle = (pwm - 1500) / 500 * multiplier + offset             │
 62 | │                                                                  │
 63 | │    Example (Channel 0 → l_hip_pitch):                            │
 64 | │    - multiplier: 1.571                                           │
 65 | │    - offset: -0.5                                                │
 66 | │    - PWM 1000 → angle = -1.571 - 0.5 = -2.071 (clamped)         │
 67 | │    - PWM 1500 → angle = 0.0 - 0.5 = -0.5                         │
 68 | │    - PWM 2000 → angle = 1.571 - 0.5 = 1.071 (clamped)           │
 69 | └────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 70 |                  │
 71 |                  │ Gazebo Topic (gz.transport)
 72 |                  │ Topic: /<joint_name>/cmd
 73 |                  │ Message: gz.msgs.Double (angle in radians)
 74 |                  │
 75 | ┌────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 76 | │ 4. GAZEBO JOINT POSITION CONTROLLER                            │
 77 | │    File: worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf                          │
 78 | │    Plugin: gz-sim-joint-position-controller-system              │
 79 | │    - Subscribes to /<joint_name>/cmd topic                       │
 80 | │    - Receives target angle (radians)                             │
 81 | │    - Applies PID control (P=8, I=0.01, D=10)                     │
 82 | │    - Clamps to joint limits                                      │
 83 | │    - Sends torque command to physics engine                      │
 84 | └────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
 85 |                  │
 86 |                  │ Physics Engine Command
 87 |                  │ Joint torque (N·m)
 88 |                  │
 89 | ┌────────────────▼────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
 90 | │ 5. GAZEBO DART PHYSICS ENGINE                                  │
 91 | │    File: worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf (physics settings)       │
 92 | │    - Receives torque command                                     │
 93 | │    - Simulates joint dynamics (mass, inertia, friction)          │
 94 | │    - Updates joint angle                                         │
 95 | │    - Timestep: 0.004s (250 Hz)                                   │
 96 | │    - Renders visual model                                        │
