<content lines="1-642">
  1 | # sdf-check
  2 | 
  3 | **Purpose:** Validate SDF joint definitions for naming consistency, friction tags, and plugin linkage.
  4 | 
  5 | **Usage:** `/sdf-check [--fix]`
  6 | 
  7 | **Options:**
  8 | - No args: Run validation checks and report issues
  9 | - `--fix`: Automatically fix common issues (duplicate friction tags, etc.)
 10 | 
 11 | ---
 12 | 
 13 | ## What This Command Does
 14 | 
 15 | Performs comprehensive validation of [`worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf`](worlds/ardupilot_humanoid.sdf) to catch common configuration errors that cause joint control failures, physics instability, or plugin mismatches. Reports all issues with line numbers and suggested fixes.
 16 | 
 17 | ---
 18 | 
 19 | ## Validation Checks
 20 | 
 21 | ### 1. Joint Naming Consistency
 22 | 
 23 | **Check:** All joint names referenced in plugins match actual joint definitions.
 24 | 
 25 | **Files Checked:**
 26 | - Joint definitions: `<joint name="...">`
 27 | - JointPositionController plugins: `<joint_name>...</joint_name>`
 28 | - ArduPilotPlugin mappings: `<jointName>...</jointName>`
 29 | 
 30 | **Common Issues:**
 31 | - Typo in plugin joint name (e.g., `l_hip_pich` vs `l_hip_pitch`)
 32 | - Plugin references non-existent joint
 33 | - Joint defined but no controller plugin
 34 | 
 35 | **Example Error:**
 36 | ```
 37 | ❌ Line 350: JointPositionController references 'l_hip_pich' but joint is named 'l_hip_pitch'
 38 | ❌ Line 125: Joint 'l_knee_shin' defined but no JointPositionController plugin found
 39 | ```
 40 | 
 41 | **Validation Logic:**
 42 | ```python
 43 | # Extract all joint names
 44 | joints = re.findall(r'<joint name="([^"]+)"', sdf_content)
 45 | 
 46 | # Extract all JointPositionController references
 47 | controller_joints = re.findall(r'<joint_name>([^<]+)</joint_name>', sdf_content)
 48 | 
 49 | # Extract all ArduPilotPlugin references
 50 | plugin_joints = re.findall(r'<jointName>([^<]+)</jointName>', sdf_content)
 51 | 
 52 | # Check for mismatches
 53 | for cj in controller_joints:
 54 |     if cj not in joints:
 55 |         print(f"❌ JointPositionController references '{cj}' but joint not defined")
 56 | 
 57 | for pj in plugin_joints:
 58 |     if pj not in joints:
 59 |         print(f"❌ ArduPilotPlugin references '{pj}' but joint not defined")
 60 | ```
 61 | 
 62 | ---
 63 | 
 64 | ### 2. Duplicate Friction Tags
 65 | 
 66 | **Check:** Joint dynamics should not have duplicate `<friction>` tags.
 67 | 
 68 | **Known Issues (AGENTS.md):**
 69 | - Lines 193, 201, 209, 220, 228, 236 have duplicate friction tags
 70 | - Gazebo uses last value, first value ignored
 71 | 
 72 | **Example:**
 73 | ```xml
 74 | <!-- WRONG: Duplicate friction tags -->
 75 | <dynamics>
 76 |   <damping>0.1</damping>
 77 |   <friction>1.5</friction>
 78 |   <friction>0.5</friction>  <!-- This value is used, 1.5 ignored -->
 79 | </dynamics>
 80 | 
 81 | <!-- CORRECT: Single friction tag -->
 82 | <dynamics>
 83 |   <damping>0.1</damping>
 84 |   <friction>0.5</friction>
 85 | </dynamics>
 86 | ```
 87 | 
 88 | **Validation Logic:**
 89 | ```python
 90 | # Find all <dynamics> blocks
 91 | dynamics_blocks = re.finditer(r'<dynamics>(.*?)</dynamics>', sdf_content, re.DOTALL)
 92 | 
 93 | for block in dynamics_blocks:
 94 |     friction_tags = re.findall(r'<friction>([^<]+)</friction>', block.group(1))
 95 |     if len(friction_tags) > 1:
 96 |         line_num = sdf_content[:block.start()].count('\n') + 1
 97 |         print(f"❌ Line {line_num}: Duplicate friction tags: {friction_tags}")
 98 |         print(f"   Gazebo will use last value: {friction_tags[-1]}")
 99 | ```
100 | 
101 | **Auto-Fix (--fix flag):**
102 | ```python
103 | # Remove duplicate friction tags, keep last value
104 | sdf_content = re.sub(
105 |     r'(<friction>[^<]+</friction>)\s*<friction>([^<]+)</friction>',
106 |     r'<friction>\2</friction>',
107 |     sdf_content
108 | )
109 | ```
110 | 
111 | ---
112 | 
113 | ### 3. Joint Limits Validation
114 | 
115 | **Check:** Joint limits are physically reasonable and match IK solver assumptions.
116 | 
117 | **Rules:**
118 | - `<lower>` must be < `<upper>`
119 | - Limits should match `inverse_kinematics.py` assumptions
120 | - Fixed joints should not have limits (or limits are ignored)
121 | 
122 | **Expected Limits (from AGENTS.md):**
123 | ```
124 | l_hip_pitch:  [-1.571, 0.523] rad  (-90° to +30°)
125 | l_knee:       [0.0, 2.618] rad     (0° to +150°)
126 | l_knee_shin:  [0.0, 2.618] rad     (0° to +150°)
127 | l_ankle:      fixed (no limits)
128 | ```
129 | 
130 | **Validation Logic:**
131 | ```python
132 | # Extract joint limits
133 | joint_limits = {}
134 | for match in re.finditer(r'<joint name="([^"]+)".*?<lower>([^<]+)</lower>.*?<upper>([^<]+)</upper>', 
135 |                           sdf_content, re.DOTALL):
136 |     name, lower, upper = match.groups()
137 |     lower, upper = float(lower), float(upper)
138 |     joint_limits[name] = (lower, upper)
139 |     
140 |     if lower >= upper:
141 |         print(f"❌ Joint '{name}': lower ({lower}) >= upper ({upper})")
142 | 
143 | # Check against IK solver expectations
144 | IK_LIMITS = {
145 |     'l_hip_pitch': (-1.57, 0.52),
146 |     'r_hip_pitch': (-1.57, 0.52),
147 |     'l_knee': (0.0, 2.618),
148 |     'r_knee': (0.0, 2.618),
149 | }
150 | 
151 | for joint, (lower, upper) in joint_limits.items():
152 |     if joint in IK_LIMITS:
153 |         ik_lower, ik_upper = IK_LIMITS[joint]
154 |         if abs(lower - ik_lower) > 0.01 or abs(upper - ik_upper) > 0.01:
155 |             print(f"⚠️  Joint '{joint}': SDF limits ({lower:.3f}, {upper:.3f}) "
156 |                   f"don't match IK solver ({ik_lower:.3f}, {ik_upper:.3f})")
157 | ```
158 | 
159 | ---
160 | 
161 | ### 4. ArduPilotPlugin Channel Mapping
162 | 
163 | **Check:** Channel mappings are complete and consistent.
164 | 
165 | **Rules:**
166 | - Each channel should map to exactly one joint
167 | - Joint names must exist in model
168 | - Multiplier should match joint range
169 | - Offset should be reasonable
170 | - No duplicate channel numbers
171 | 
172 | **Expected Mapping:**
173 | ```
174 | CH0 → l_hip_pitch (mult=1.571, offset=-0.5)
175 | CH1 → r_hip_pitch (mult=1.571, offset=-0.5)
176 | CH2 → l_knee      (mult=2.618, offset=-0.5)
177 | CH3 → r_knee      (mult=2.618, offset=-0.5)
178 | ```
179 | 
180 | **Validation Logic:**
181 | ```python
182 | # Extract channel mappings
183 | channels = {}
184 | for match in re.finditer(r'<control channel="(\d+)">(.*?)</control>', sdf_content, re.DOTALL):
185 |     ch_num = int(match.group(1))
186 |     ch_block = match.group(2)
187 |     
188 |     joint = re.search(r'<jointName>([^<]+)</jointName>', ch_block).group(1)
189 |     mult = float(re.search(r'<multiplier>([^<]+)</multiplier>', ch_block).group(1))
190 |     offset = float(re.search(r'<offset>([^<]+)</offset>', ch_block).group(1))
191 |     
192 |     if ch_num in channels:
193 |         print(f"❌ Channel {ch_num} mapped to multiple joints: "
194 |               f"{channels[ch_num]['joint']} and {joint}")
195 |     
196 |     channels[ch_num] = {'joint': joint, 'mult': mult, 'offset': offset}
197 | 
198 | # Check multipliers match joint ranges
199 | for ch_num, cfg in channels.items():
200 |     joint = cfg['joint']
201 |     mult = cfg['mult']
202 |     
203 |     if joint in joint_limits:
204 |         lower, upper = joint_limits[joint]
205 |         expected_mult = max(abs(lower), abs(upper))
206 |         
207 |         if abs(mult - expected_mult) > 0.1:
208 |             print(f"⚠️  Channel {ch_num} ({joint}): multiplier {mult:.3f} "
209 |                   f"doesn't match joint range (expected ~{expected_mult:.3f})")
210 | ```
211 | 
212 | ---
213 | 
214 | ### 5. JointPositionController Configuration
215 | 
216 | **Check:** Each movable joint has a position controller with reasonable PID gains.
217 | 
218 | **Rules:**
219 | - Every revolute joint should have a controller
220 | - Fixed joints should not have controllers (or controller is ignored)
221 | - Topic name should match `/<joint_name>/cmd`
222 | - PID gains should be reasonable (P=5-10, I=0.01, D=5-15)
223 | - Initial position should match standing pose
224 | 
225 | **Expected Configuration:**
226 | ```xml
227 | <plugin filename="gz-sim-joint-position-controller-system">
228 |   <joint_name>l_hip_pitch</joint_name>
229 |   <topic>/l_hip_pitch/cmd</topic>
230 |   <p_gain>8</p_gain>
231 |   <i_gain>0.01</i_gain>
232 |   <d_gain>10</d_gain>
233 |   <initial_position>-0.09</initial_position>
234 | </plugin>
235 | ```
236 | 
237 | **Validation Logic:**
238 | ```python
239 | # Extract all revolute joints
240 | revolute_joints = []
241 | for match in re.finditer(r'<joint name="([^"]+)" type="revolute"', sdf_content):
242 |     revolute_joints.append(match.group(1))
243 | 
244 | # Extract all JointPositionController configs
245 | controllers = {}
246 | for match in re.finditer(r'<plugin filename="gz-sim-joint-position-controller-system".*?>(.*?)</plugin>', 
247 |                           sdf_content, re.DOTALL):
248 |     block = match.group(1)
249 |     joint = re.search(r'<joint_name>([^<]+)</joint_name>', block).group(1)
250 |     topic = re.search(r'<topic>([^<]+)</topic>', block).group(1)
251 |     p_gain = float(re.search(r'<p_gain>([^<]+)</p_gain>', block).group(1))
252 |     i_gain = float(re.search(r'<i_gain>([^<]+)</i_gain>', block).group(1))
253 |     d_gain = float(re.search(r'<d_gain>([^<]+)</d_gain>', block).group(1))
254 |     
255 |     controllers[joint] = {'topic': topic, 'p': p_gain, 'i': i_gain, 'd': d_gain}
256 |     
257 |     # Check topic name
258 |     expected_topic = f"/{joint}/cmd"
259 |     if topic != expected_topic:
260 |         print(f"❌ Joint '{joint}': topic '{topic}' should be '{expected_topic}'")
261 |     
262 |     # Check PID gains
263 |     if p_gain < 1 or p_gain > 20:
264 |         print(f"⚠️  Joint '{joint}': P gain {p_gain} outside typical range (5-10)")
265 |     if d_gain < 1 or d_gain > 20:
266 |         print(f"⚠️  Joint '{joint}': D gain {d_gain} outside typical range (5-15)")
267 | 
268 | # Check all revolute joints have controllers
269 | for joint in revolute_joints:
270 |     if joint not in controllers:
271 |         print(f"❌ Revolute joint '{joint}' has no JointPositionController")
272 | ```
273 | 
274 | ---
