329 | ### 7. Physics Configuration
330 | 
331 | **Check:** Physics settings are stable and reasonable.
332 | 
333 | **Rules:**
334 | - `max_step_size` ≤ 0.004s (CRITICAL - larger causes explosions)
335 | - `real_time_factor` = 1.0 (real-time simulation)
336 | - Physics engine = DART (required for humanoid stability)
337 | 
338 | **Expected Configuration:**
339 | ```xml
340 | <physics name="1ms" type="dart">
341 |   <max_step_size>0.004</max_step_size>
342 |   <real_time_factor>1</real_time_factor>
343 | </physics>
344 | ```
345 | 
346 | **Validation Logic:**
347 | ```python
348 | # Extract physics settings
349 | physics_match = re.search(r'<physics name="[^"]*" type="([^"]+)">(.*?)</physics>', 
350 |                           sdf_content, re.DOTALL)
351 | if physics_match:
352 |     engine = physics_match.group(1)
353 |     block = physics_match.group(2)
354 |     
355 |     if engine != "dart":
356 |         print(f"❌ Physics engine '{engine}' should be 'dart' for humanoid stability")
357 |     
358 |     step_size = float(re.search(r'<max_step_size>([^<]+)</max_step_size>', block).group(1))
359 |     if step_size > 0.004:
360 |         print(f"❌ CRITICAL: max_step_size {step_size}s > 0.004s (robot will explode!)")
361 |     
362 |     rtf = float(re.search(r'<real_time_factor>([^<]+)</real_time_factor>', block).group(1))
363 |     if rtf != 1.0:
364 |         print(f"⚠️  real_time_factor {rtf} != 1.0 (simulation not real-time)")
365 | ```
